2. **`parseJsonIfPossible` Function**: This function checks if the stripped text starts with a JSON object or array and attempts to parse it. If parsing fails, it returns `null`.
3. **`processText` Function**: This is the main function that combines the above two functions to process the input text.

This refactoring makes each part of the logic more modular and easier to understand and maintain.

